The paper deals with the problem of estimating an additive functional of a discrete distribution, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of the divergence speed of the fourth derivative of a function, which is a topic in mathematical analysis and optimization (cs.DS). The problem of estimating a functional from i.i.d. samples is a common problem in statistics (cs.ST) and the paper proposes a minimax optimal estimator, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
